peopleAlsoAsk.question: Are old bells worth anything?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Older bells command higher prices than newer bells, all other things being equal. Is the bell historical, antique, or modern? What form does the bell take? Is it a standard cup shape, does it have balanced proportions, is there a uniqueness that sets it apart from other bells?

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What are antique bells made of?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Historic church and tower bells were sometimes cast from brass, iron, or steel, which were more economical to manufacture than bronze. Decorative bells can be made from any number of materials at hand, including glass, horn, wood, clay, copper, or precious metals.
